  "texts": [
    "The GlideSP redocking score involves docking the generated molecules into the pocket, including the exploration of ligand binding conformations and initial placement.",
    "Among the three docking-related metrics for binding pose evaluation, we advocate using the min-in-place GlideSP score for the following reasons.",
    "The in-place GlideSP score is excessively sensitive to atomic distances between the ligand and pocket, making it unsuitable for evaluating the quality of generated poses.",
    "In Extended Data Table 3, most molecules generated by all three methods (Lingo3DMol, Pocket2Mol and TargetDiff) exhibit positive scores, indicating steric clashes between the pockets and ligands.",
    "However, such clashes do not necessarily denote a poor molecule unless they cannot be rectified by force-field-based minimization."
